Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` ≈ iOS `WillResignActive` (lost focus, may still be visible)
- Android `OnStop` ≈ iOS `DidEnterBackground` (fully backgrounded)
- Keep handlers fast (<5s on Android, limited time on iOS) to avoid ANR/watchdog kills

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback arguments, use the `Window.Stopped` event instead — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* runs on both platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```
